instance_each.description:
Loops through every element of the instance collection and applies the given callback function to it.

The signature of the callback function is <code>(element, [i]) => {...}</code>. Elements that are not <code>HTMLElement</code> (e.g. <code>Comment</code> or text nodes) are <i>not</i> processed.

Click the [Try it] button twice and watch the method name headers for a demo.

<example>
const mNameElems = $(`.methodName`);
const brown = `rgb(165, 42, 42)`;
const currentColor = mNameElems.computedStyle(`color`);
mNameElems.each( el => $(el).style({color: currentColor === brown ? `` : brown}) );
</example>
<button class="exRunBttn" data-action="eachEx">Try it</button>

instance_computedStyle.description:
Retrieves the computed style for the given <code>property</code> the first element of the instance collection.

See also <div class="linkLike" data-action="jump2Nav" data-jumpkey="instance_Style">Style.computed</div>.

<example>
  $.editCssRule(`.redEx {color: red; font-weight: bold}`);
  $(`<p class="redEx">Hello!</p>`, /*[root element]*/);
  popup.show( {content: `$(".redEx").computedStyle("color"): ${ $(`.redEx`).computedStyle(`color`) }
  <br>$(".redEx").computedStyle("font-weight"): ${ $(`.redEx`).computedStyle(`font-weight`) }` } );
</example>
<button class="exRunBttn" data-action="computedStyleEx">Try it</button>

instance_isEmpty.description:
returns: <code>true</code> if the JQL Instance collection is empty, otherwise <code>false</code>.

<b>Note</b>: alternatively you can use <code>[JQL instance].is.empty</code>.

<example>
const someDiv = $(`<div data-id="tmpEx">
  <b>Hello</b>! <span></span></div>`,  /*[root element]*/);
popup.show( {content: `<code>someDiv.isEmpty()</code> =&gt; ${someDiv.isEmpty()}
  <br><code>someDiv.find$("span:first-child").isEmpty()</code> =&gt; ${
    someDiv.find$(`span:first-child`).isEmpty()}`, callback: () => $(`[data-id="tmpEx"]`).remove()} );
</example>
<button class="exRunBttn" data-action="isEmptyEx">Try it</button>

instance_getData.description:
Retrieve the value of a data-attribute. When <code>valueWhenFalsy</code> is present, it will return that value if the data-attribute does not exist.

<b>See also</b>: <div class="linkLike" data-action="jump2Nav" data-jumpkey="instance_data">data</div>.

<example>
const popup = $.popup();
const thisBttn = $(evt.target);
const action = thisBttn.getData(`action`);
const undef = thisBttn.getData(`nonexistent`);
const undefWithDefaultValue = thisBttn.getData(`nothing`, `NOCANDO`);
popup.show( {content: [`action: ${action}`, `undef: ${undef}`, `undefWithDefaultValue: ${undefWithDefaultValue}`].join(`<br>`)} );
</example>
<button class="exRunBttn" data-action="getDataEx">Try it</button>

instance_replace.description:
Replace [oldChild] (a DOM Element, css selector or a JQL instance) within the first (root) element of the instance element collection with a new JQL Instance

<example>
const div = $.virtual(`
  <div>Hi there! 
    <div class="oldD">I shall be replaced...</div>
    <div class="oldD">Me Too!</div>
  </div>`);
const newDiv = $.virtual(`<div>Formerly known as "div.oldD"<div>`).style({color: `red`});
popup.show( {
  content: div,
  closeAfter: 3,
  callback: () => popup.show({
    content: div.replace(`.oldD`, newDiv),
    closeAfter: 3
  }),
});
</example>
<button class="exRunBttn" data-action="replaceEx">Try it</button>

instance_replaceMe.description:
Replace the JQL Instance with a new JQL Instance. 

<b>Note</b>: If the new instance is <div class="linkLike" data-action="jump2Nav" data-jumpkey="static_virtual">virtual</div>, it will be added to the DOM tree on replacement.

<example>
const oldDiv = $.virtual(`<div id="oldD">I shall be replaced...<div>`);
const newDiv = $.virtual(`<div id="newD">I have replaced div#oldD!<div>`);
popup.show( {
  content: oldDiv,
  closeAfter: 3,
  callback: () => popup.show({
      content: oldDiv.replaceMe(newDiv).style({color: `red`}),
      closeAfter: 3
    }),
});
</example>
<button class="exRunBttn" data-action="replaceMeEx">Try it</button>

instance_first.description:
Returns the first element of the JQL element collection or a new JQL Instance derived from the first element of the JQL Instance element collection. When <code>asJQLInstance</code> is true, the element is returned as a new JQL Instance (equivalent to <div data-action="jump2Nav" data-jumpkey="instance_first$" class="linkLike">first$</div>), otherwise a <code>DOM Node</code>.

<example>
const jqlElems = $(`#navigation li[data-key]`);
popup.show( {content: $(`
