instance_html.description:
Get (inner-) html of the first (root) element in the collection of the JQL instance <i>or</i> set html for each element of the collection.

Overwrites current html of the elements, or appends (<code>append</code>: true) the value to it. 

<b>Note</b>: <code>htmlValue</code> is always sanitized.

<example>
const someDiv = $(`<div data-id="tmpEx">
  Hello <span>world</span>
</div>`, /*[root element]*/);
setTimeout(() => {
  $(`[data-id="tmpEx"] span`, , /*[root element]*/).html(`universe!`);
  setTimeout(() => $(`[data-id="tmpEx"] span`, /*[root element]*/).html(` And by again`, true), 1500);
}, 1500);
</example>
