instance_htmlFor.description:
Sets/adds/removes html for an element within the collection of the JQL Instance (identified with a css query).

<b>Note</b>: html from <code>htmlString</code> is always sanitized.

<b>Note</b>: if <code>htmlString</code> is empty, the element content is removed.

<example>
const someDiv = $(`<div data-id="tmpEx">
  Hello <span><b>world</b></span> <span>etc.</span>
  </div>`, /* root element */);
setTimeout(() => {
  popup.show( {
    content: someDiv.duplicate().htmlFor(`span:first-child`, `<i><b>UNIVERSE</b></i>`),
    callback: () => $(`[data-id="tmpEx"]`).remove(),
    closeAfter: 5 });
}, 1500);
</example>
