instance_HTML.description:
Returns a utility object for retrieving inner-/outerHTML, replacing, inserting or appending html of the first element of the JQL instance element.

The available methods:
<ul>
<li><code>get([outer:boolean, escaped:boolean])</code> Retrieves the html. If [outer] is true, it will be the outerHTML, otherwise innerHTML. When [escaped] is true, the html will be escaped, meaning that you can display the html within another html element.</li>
<li><code>replace(html:string|JQL Instance)</code> Replace the innerHTML with [string]</li>
<li><code>append(html:string|JQL Instance)</code> Appends [string] to innerHTML</li>
<li><code>insert(html:string|JQL Instance)</code> Inserts [string] to innerHTML</li>
</ul>
<b>Notes</b>:

<ul><li><code>replace</code>, <code>append</code> and <code>insert</code> return the JQL instance.</li>
<li>When the [html] parameter is a JQL Instance, the outer HTML of the first element of its collection will be used.</li></ul>


<example>
const emptyEl = $.virtual(`<div>'nough said</div>`);
const html = emptyEl.HTML;
const emptyElOuterHtml1 = `created emptyEl: ${html.get(true, true)}`;
html.replace(`HELLO`);
const emptyElOuterHtml2 = `replace: ${html.get(true, true)}`;
html.append($(`<span> WORLD</span>`));
const emptyElOuterHtml3 = `append: ${html.get(true, true)}`;
const emptyElOuterHtml4 = `insert: ${html.insert($(`<b>the obligatory ...</b> `)).HTML.get(true, true)}`;
// aggregate
const report = $.virtual(`<div>${emptyElOuterHtml1}<br>${emptyElOuterHtml2}<br>${
  emptyElOuterHtml3}<br>${emptyElOuterHtml4}<br>So, there we have it:</div>`).append(emptyEl);
popup.show({ content: report } );
</example>
<button class="exRunBttn" data-action="htmlObjEx">Try it</button>

static_editCssRules.description:
Add one or more css rules (e.g. <code>.redBold {color: red; font-weight: bold;}</code>) to <code>&lt;style id="JQLStylesheet"></code>.

<example>
const div1 = $.virtual(`<div id="div1">I am div#div1</div>`);
const div2 = $.virtual(`<div id="div2">I am div#div2</div>`);
$.editCssRules(
  `#div1 {margin: 0.3rem; color: green; background-color: #EEE; }`,
  `#div2 {margin: 0.3rem; color: red; background-color: #EEE; }` );
popup.show( {
  content: $.virtual(`<div>`).append(div1, div2),
  callback: () => $.removeCssRule(`#div1`, `#div2`) } );
</example>
